survey.music_making: Not a musician, but I have been singing longer than I could talk. I participated in musicals in school and I took lessons in sax and trombone, but i always loved to sing. I tried to start a girl group, but that didn't work. I performed for a producer for Earth, Wind, and Fire and he wanted me to move to LA so he could train me but i didn't want to be so far away from my family on the East Coast.
survey.medium: Radio, Sirius XM, Tidal, YouTube, Twitch, Instagram, concerts
survey.activities: I do almost everything to music. Even working and occasionally sleeping with binaural beats. Not constantly, but regularly.
survey.habit_change: My habits really have not changed. I have always been an old soul and listened to most genres and subgenres of music over various decades. I think the greatest change for me is the mediums from which I am listening, From Using my grandfather's 8-track and my father's LPs and 45s to having my own cassettes and radio, and then having my first car with a CD player, to using my SiriusXM radio and various other streaming services.
survey.habits: I think I covered most things in question 12
